<p style="text-align: justify;">There are several important factors to consider when you are seeking for an <strong>outsourcing partner in the Philippines</strong>. The U.S. is still recovering from an economic downturn and this has forced the global companies of various sizes from all over the world to realize the high value of outsourcing their vital processes from the Philippines. Nevertheless, realizing and making a decision on who to entrust your businessâ€™ processes with is one thing, walking the talk is entirely another thing. For those who seek to find the right outsourcing partners; they must find the right provider of BPO (business process outsourcing) to collude with. This paper will list the five crucial factors considered when choosing the right <strong>outsourcing partner in the Philippines</strong> who will satisfy your needs.</p>

<ol>
 	<li>
<h2 style="font-size: x-large;"><strong>Lowest Cost Provider</strong></h2>
</li>
</ol>
<p style="text-align: justify;">When you employ a BPO company from the Philippines for your business processes, you are sure to save a lot. This is because, the Philippines is cheaper compared to other countries. However, the initial expenses could be quite expensive; but afterwards, the cost of running the investment is cheaper but still cost effective. Therefore, it is important to thoroughly research the prospect that best suits your investments.</p>

<ol start="2">
 	<li>
<h2 style="font-size: x-large;"><strong>Focus on employee engagement to reduce attrition</strong></h2>
</li>
</ol>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Every company has its unique features, therefore, it is vital that you look for the business process outsourcing provider which will match your companyâ€™s objectives, business ideals and strengths. This will ensure that all your needs are addressed, and there would be a better understanding between you and your outsourcing partner, hence a great working relationship. A good working relationship would be good for your business because it will provide a good environment for the business to prosper. Moreover, this good relationship will make your BPO tailor the best solutions and services which will address all your needs and also be at your disposal whenever you need help during the expansion of your business.</p>

<ol start="3">
 	<li>
<h2 style="font-size: x-large;"><strong>Flexibility in meeting your needs</strong></h2>
</li>
</ol>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The outsourcing partner you have to choose must incorporate and meet your demands during the provision of their services. To meet these standards, proper infrastructure must be in place; the infrastructure must come with high class software and hardware components, good network structure, redundant internet connections, not to mention the technologies which are specific to your industrial needs. Besides all the factors, you should also look for an<strong> outsourcing partner in the Philippines</strong> which have a high capability of adapting to new technologies whenever you incorporate the latest devices in your company/industry.</p>

<ol start="4">
 	<li>
<h2 style="font-size: x-large;"><strong>Professional working environment</strong></h2>
</li>
</ol>
<p style="text-align: justify;">It is vital to take into consideration the professional working environment as one of your priorities when looking for an outsourcing partner. You have to inquire about the professionalism that the outsourcing partner has in place and their abilities to manage risks.</p>

<ol start="5">
 	<li>
<h2 style="font-size: x-large;"><strong>Focus on employee engagement to reduce attrition </strong></h2>
</li>
</ol>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Employee engagement guarantees your businessâ€™ growth and safety because employee engagement empowers your business with personal touch. Without employee engagement, sensitive information can be leaked and consequently destroy your competence in the market. Therefore, your partner has to provide best employees with full devotion and engagement with work.</p>

<ol start="6">
 	<li>
<h2 style="font-size: x-large;"><strong>Track record in risk assessment</strong></h2>
</li>
</ol>
<p style="text-align: justify;">A credible and reliable BPO company must come with comprehensive risk assessment guidelines which will clearly identify the potential risks that could be detrimental to your business, and in turn, place adequate measures which will prevent these risks from occurring. There must also be risk management protocols in case disasters occur. Measures like redundant storage, use of backup systems and any other relevant data protection measures have to be implemented.</p>

<ol start="7">
 	<li>
<h2 style="font-size: x-large;"><strong>Hands on owners/founders</strong></h2>
</li>
</ol>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The workforce is what will dictate the smoothness of your operations in the Philippines. Therefore, it is vital that you entrust your business operations to people who possess adequate skills, discipline and knowledge for the job. These requirements apply to all the personnel starting from the top ranked supervisors to the low-level employees. Therefore, to get the right partner for you, you will have to dig deeper into the prospects hiring process. This will further be helpful in the situation where your business operations demand some qualifications like technical skills, talents and work experience.</p>

<h2 style="font-size: x-large;"><strong>CONCLUSION </strong></h2>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Delegating your companyâ€™s processes to BPO service providers comes with its advantages because it offers you the efficiency of continuously running the operations at a much lesser cost while also retaining your in-house employees. However, before embarking on the creation of your outsourcing plans, it is vital that you look for a trustworthy and reliable <strong>outsourcing partner in the Philippines</strong>. The partner you choose has to have powerful infrastructure and a tremendous workforce which will not only smoothen the running of your operations but also elevate your competence in the market, hence propelling you to success.</p>
